10:
Well, I never... Looks like these
Eastern newcomers haven't a speck
of refinement!
19:
Now, where's that young diviner
man when you need him?
24:
The Commission is meeting
tonight... So the Chair can't be here...
26: Th-that's why I've come in his place.
29:
Oh my. Are you sure you can handle
this, dearie?
31: Y-yes... It'll be over in an instant...
35:
Hehe. Very well then. Show us what
you're made of!
41:
Snake that slithers along ocean
floor...
Bind your foes so they move
nevermore!
56:
Well, now that THIS mess has been
cleaned up, it's back to—
60: What's a diviner doing with yokai?
63:
Oh bother. I should've seen this
coming. The East isn't quite
accustomed to friendly yokai.
70:
I recognize that girl... She works for
the tengu boy!
72:
You mean that diviner brat? So his
parents really are yokai...
74: Have they been playing us for fools?!
91:
Get a hold of yourself! You're
stronger than this!
93:
Oh, fine! Awa, Hie, Mugi! Fetch the
sleigh!
100: Are you ready to fly, Stella?
113:
Finally awake, are you? Goodness.
When it comes to being a heavy
sleeper, you give even the princess
a run for her money.
120:
No need to worry. There aren't any of
your detested "humans" about.
126:
Well, you do detest them, don’t you?
Humans.
129:
My, you haven't even realized yet.
Well, you'd better open your eyes
soon, young lady.
130:
If not, that snake will strangle you in
your sleep.
132:
Well. We REALLY need to get going
now. Only the deities know what
mess the kitchen will be in.
138:
You don't have anything to say
about me... disliking humans?
141:
Don't let the negativity consume
you. Intense hate can warp the spirit
AND the body. Just give it a few
hundred years.
146:
Anger, loathing... Best to let go of
those feelings when you can. But
there's no forcing yourself to feel a
certain way.
148:
And if you happen to have a slight...
distaste for humans... I don't see
much of a problem with that.
155:
As Alk says... Everything in
moderation.
159:
All right. Then I'll keep disliking
them... in moderation.
164:
Now, IF you don't mind, we must be
going home now.
